// altium-cruncher pcb-svg configuration
// This file is JSONC: // comments, /* block comments */, and trailing commas are accepted.

// Schema: pcb.svg.config.a0

// Common physical layer tokens: TOP, BOTTOM, TOPOVERLAY, BOTTOMOVERLAY, TOPPASTE,
//   BOTTOMPASTE, TOPSOLDER, BOTTOMSOLDER, and MECHANICAL_1..MECHANICAL_32.

// Synthetic layer tokens: BOARD_OUTLINE, BOARD_CUTOUTS, DRILLS, SLOTS,
//   ASSEMBLY_HLR_TOP, ASSEMBLY_HLR_BOTTOM,
//   ASSEMBLY_DESIGNATORS_TOP, ASSEMBLY_DESIGNATORS_BOTTOM, PIN1_TOP, PIN1_BOTTOM.

// In each view, the layers array is the draw order. HLR renders last, and
//   DRILLS/SLOTS render immediately before HLR.

// With .PrjPcb input, add global.pcbdoc to select one specific board.

// Default composed views include top/bottom, board_cutouts, top/bottom pin-1,
//   and top/bottom HLR bounding-box inspection views.

/*
HLR modes:
  bounding_box - pad-bounds rectangle; no Geometer/STEP projection.
  simple       - Geometer simple outline, with pad-bounds fallback when no STEP model is available.
  detail       - Geometer detailed visible projection, with pad-bounds fallback when no STEP model is available.
  none         - suppress HLR projection.

Assembly HLR style override example, globally, inside any view.styles,
or inside components.<designator>.assembly_hlr for a single part:
  "assembly_hlr": {
    "enabled": true,
    "color": "#F59E0B",
    "line_width_mm": 0.12,
    "projection_algorithm": "exact",
    "curve_mode": "native_arcs",
    "samples_per_curve": 24,
    "round_digits": 3,
    "include_visible": true,
    "include_outline": true,
    "union_polygons": true,
    "mesh_linear_deflection": 0.01,
    "mesh_angular_deflection": 0.5,
    "mesh_relative": false,
    "hlr_angle_tolerance": 0.0174533
  }

Geometer pass-through settings currently accepted by assembly_hlr include:
  projection_algorithm, mesh_linear_deflection, mesh_angular_deflection,
  mesh_relative, hlr_angle_tolerance, and edge flags like edge_h_outline.

Component override examples:

  "components": {
    "J1": {"projection": "none"},
    "U5": {"pin1_pad": "B1", "assembly_hlr": {"color": "#2563EB"}},
    "TP1": {"pin1_enabled": false},
    "R12": {"pin1_enabled": true},
    "D15": {
      "projection": "bounding_box",
      "cathode_pad": "C",
      "assembly_hlr": {"line_width_mm": 0.2, "mesh_linear_deflection": 0.02}
    }
  }

Projection modes: detail, simple, bounding_box, none.
Use DRILLS/SLOTS plus drills.non_plated_color and slots.non_plated_color
to show non-plated holes separately from plated holes.

Pin-1 exclusions:
  pin1.exclude_designator_prefixes uses the alphabetic refdes prefix.
  ["R", "C", "L"] excludes R1/R2, C1/C2, and L1/L2.
  A component override such as "R12": {"pin1_enabled": true}
  turns pin-1 marking back on for that specific component.
*/

